WEBVTT

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:04.399
Hey, good morning family. Praise the Lord. Thank you for joining us today.

00:00:04.400 --> 00:00:12.008
Well, we want to take the time right now just to thank all our servicemen and women. I know a lot of you don't get enough appreciation.

00:00:12.009 --> 00:00:24.719
I feel in my heart there's a lot of you that are still going through the trials of war, from your body being mangled up to all kinds of things.

00:00:24.720 --> 00:00:33.373
You know, there's men that have lost their wives, there's women that have lost their husbands, and fathers and mothers that have lost their sons and daughters.

00:00:33.374 --> 00:00:46.980
And I want to just take the time to say thank you. Thank you. Thank you for sacrificing your life to make America great. Because of people like you, we're free.

00:00:46.981 --> 00:01:02.874
Because of people like you that have fought in those trenches, and went and got drafted in Vietnam, and all the terrible things of war, the things that you have seen, we pray peace over you today.

00:01:02.875 --> 00:01:11.526
We pray peace over your mind today. We pray peace that passes all understanding over you.

00:01:11.527 --> 00:01:24.032
I know there's a lot of you; you email me and you tell me, "I'm battling with PTSD, and I have nightmares every night."And my goodness, I pray peace over you.

00:01:24.033 --> 00:01:37.674
We know your sacrifice was great, and many people will never understand that sacrifice because they've not walked it.

00:01:37.675 --> 00:01:43.495
And so we just want to take the time to say thank you. Thank you for our country.

00:01:43.496 --> 00:01:47.965
Thank you for fighting for us. Because of you, we're not speaking another language.

00:01:47.966 --> 00:01:52.671
We're Americans and we just want to say thank you. God bless you.

00:01:52.672 --> 00:01:57.258
So, we're going to go over some of the things that we spoke about last time in the last video.

00:01:57.259 --> 00:02:05.290
You know, folks, I believe in God for big. That is my motto. It's what I teach my kids.

00:02:05.291 --> 00:02:09.432
That's what I teach. That's what my wife and I—we don't want to think small.

00:02:09.433 --> 00:02:15.359
You know, it's like Oral Roberts said, "Make no little plans here."It's all over his campus.

00:02:15.360 --> 00:02:24.994
"Make no little plans here. Think big. Think big."So when you drive around, it's like Oral Roberts University. You can go there so many times. I go out there all the time.

00:02:24.995 --> 00:02:32.728
Drive by every day almost and look at the campus because it inspires me to think and believe big—that that was somebody's faith, you know.

00:02:32.729 --> 00:02:47.074
And so when I talk about driving around cars, I really don't have a desire to have a fleet load of cars, but I think that's the best the world has to offer: Cadillacs, Range Rovers.

00:02:47.075 --> 00:02:52.727
That's what the Hollywood movie stars drive, you know. And, you know, we don't have a Rolls-Royce dealership or Ferrari.

00:02:52.728 --> 00:02:57.566
I drive around in those to inspire yourself to think bigger.

00:02:57.567 --> 00:03:16.209
When you're raised in poverty, when you're raised in what I was raised in, you don't have an inward image of wealth to think bigger for God to do bigger because you're so used to thinking small.

00:03:16.210 --> 00:03:21.482
You know, grandma was poor, her grandma was poor, everybody's been poor, and you'll be poor, too.

00:03:21.483 --> 00:03:26.902
No, I'm redeemed from the curse. And I believe poverty is a curse, regardless.

00:03:26.903 --> 00:03:32.672
I've never seen anybody that's not able to pay their bills, struggling and eating Spam and doing things.

00:03:32.673 --> 00:03:37.433
Well, people say, "I like Spam."Well, I don't. I don't. I personally don't. That's my opinion.

00:03:37.434 --> 00:03:51.067
So you know, you have people that are raised on certain things—Ramen noodles and things that you go, "Well, that's all we had because that's what we could afford."Living on food stamps, living on these things.

00:03:51.068 --> 00:03:55.700
That's a curse. True poverty is a curse. It's not a blessing.

00:03:55.701 --> 00:04:09.072
And people, you live in some of these remote areas in Haiti and Africa and in Asia or whatever, and you're living in a tin hut or whatever—that's not a blessing.

00:04:09.073 --> 00:04:13.419
I look at what everybody goes to work for Monday through Friday.

00:04:13.420 --> 00:04:27.601
The reason I say it, and I'm so strong about it, is because we all go to work every day to try to make the dream, to get enough money to put your kids through college, to pay your bills on time so they don't repo your car.

00:04:27.602 --> 00:04:33.185
I've been there, and I know that those times were sorrowful. That was hard.

00:04:33.186 --> 00:04:48.716
And believing God to get extra, selling on eBay and Poshmark and doing these things that we've done, stepping out by faith and finding things. There's even another level of, I see, wealth.

00:04:48.717 --> 00:04:59.316
And the Bible says, "Beloved, I wish above all things that you prosper and be in health, even as your soul prospers."There's so much in the Bible about walking in abundance.

00:04:59.317 --> 00:05:05.106
In abundance to the full, till it overflows. Not living barely getting by and broke.

00:05:05.107 --> 00:05:23.679
And yeah, people got you burned out because of the prosperity preaching and all that stuff, but I believe a lot of them started out good, trying to help out the body of Christ to break off the yoke of bondage, because I'm telling you, there's a lot of bondage with poverty.

00:05:23.680 --> 00:05:34.857
And I'm not saying that there's no bondage with prosperity, because there are a lot of people that lose themselves in it, and it is what it is.

00:05:34.858 --> 00:05:42.613
But I think there's a happy medium that you can have blessing as long as the blessing doesn't have you.

00:05:42.614 --> 00:05:54.253
So, that's what I'm talking about: getting that inward image of the blessing and walking in an abundance so you can help those around you. Help those around you.

00:05:54.254 --> 00:06:12.260
I've seen people—man, I wish, you know, you drive by and you see somebody that they don't have nothing, you're looking at them going, "Man, I wish I had a little extra to help them out."But there's so much blockage in the mind when it comes to the devil trying to tell you you can't have nothing.

00:06:12.261 --> 00:06:21.038
He doesn't wrestle with you trying to bless you. You know what happened with me? Let me tell you. I'll be real with you right now.

00:06:21.039 --> 00:06:28.963
Satan himself came to my house, and I used the visions that I have—he showed me all the wealth.

00:06:28.964 --> 00:06:40.813
He said, "If you bow your knee to me, if you bow your knee to me, I will give you all this wealth."I saw jets, I saw houses, I saw Ferraris, I saw all this.

00:06:40.814 --> 00:06:52.851
He said, "If you serve me and use the gift that you have for seeing for the kingdom of darkness, I will give you everything that your heart's desire."He showed it all to me.

00:06:52.852 --> 00:07:08.030
I saw his palace, and it was black onyx, and blood was flowing from his throne, and it was just similar to what happened, I believe, to what happened to Jesus: "If you serve me, I'll give you all this.

00:07:08.031 --> 00:07:24.505
I'll give you the kingdoms of the earth."To make a long story short, because I don't like talking about the darkness, there's nothing the devil has to offer in all that that I wanted.

00:07:24.506 --> 00:07:30.079
I want the anointing. I want the presence of the Father. And in Him, there's peace.

00:07:30.080 --> 00:07:37.619
There's joy. There's all those things. The devil has nothing good to offer.

00:07:37.620 --> 00:07:45.872
I've had, what, three visitations like that. The last one was to challenge the Word.

00:07:45.873 --> 00:07:50.746
And he spoke to me, and I said, "Are you coming to offer the kingdoms again?"And he said, "No.

00:07:50.747 --> 00:07:54.194
Once you reject me once, I never come and offer you anything again.

00:07:54.195 --> 00:08:05.679
I'm coming to challenge the Word."You know, like I said, I don't talk about the darkness.

00:08:05.680 --> 00:08:12.272
But I want you to know that even the devil tries to entice people with wealth.

00:08:12.273 --> 00:08:19.293
Why? Because it's what the world wants. We wake up every day, Monday through Friday, like I said.

00:08:19.294 --> 00:08:29.928
But how much can you be a believing believer and have it, and show the world that you can have Jesus and the blessing? You can have Jesus and the blessing.

00:08:29.929 --> 00:08:39.653
So, that's not my message for today, but I feel like a lot of people are hung up on poverty, and I refuse to take that vow.

00:08:39.654 --> 00:08:47.917
I refuse to take it for my kids. I want generational wealth. I'm believing for what He showed me about the cryptocurrencies.

00:08:47.918 --> 00:08:54.370
I'm believing for what He showed me about gold and silver, and what He showed me about these things.

00:08:54.371 --> 00:09:04.077
And I'm standing on what the Lord has showed me. I stand on that. Now, everything the Lord does, it's like I told Dino.

00:09:04.078 --> 00:09:06.268
We were talking about the anointing and the increase of the anointing.

00:09:06.269 --> 00:09:11.842
It seems to go with the price of the anointing and the price of walking in the glory.

00:09:11.843 --> 00:09:19.940
It seems to go through—you seem to go through the winepress where you feel the pressure of things.

00:09:19.941 --> 00:09:32.590
The character it takes to sustain it costs you something. You can't get that in the world.

00:09:32.591 --> 00:09:38.815
You can't walk in that kind of glory from the world. The devil can't offer that.

00:09:38.816 --> 00:09:42.958
What that is, is it's coming straight out of the throne room.

00:09:42.959 --> 00:09:46.026
And it was all bought and paid for by the blood of Jesus, folks.

00:09:46.027 --> 00:09:49.397
But I'm telling you, there is a price to pay for the anointing.

00:09:49.398 --> 00:09:57.805
There is a price to pay for walking in the glory. It comes through pressure.

00:09:57.806 --> 00:10:04.072
It comes through the refiner's fire. And most people don't want to hear that.

00:10:04.072 --> 00:10:13.622
But I've studied and I've looked at every single person that has walked in a great anointing, and they've all had a refiner's fire.

00:10:13.623 --> 00:10:32.488
They've all had pressure on them to the point where I thought, 'Does it look like they could make it out of it?'where your head is pulled underneath that water and you're grasping for air, and all you want and all you think about is just to get your next breath.

00:10:32.489 --> 00:10:39.247
It comes out of that pressure. How bad do you want change? How bad do you want the glory?

00:10:39.248 --> 00:10:47.597
How bad do you want the anointing on your life? It comes through something: the press, an oil press.

00:10:47.598 --> 00:11:00.198
Like whenever you see those olive oil presses and they're pressing that oil, and the more that oil presses down on there and clamps down on there, it presses all that good oil out of those olives.

00:11:00.199 --> 00:11:13.119
That's the way it is with you. Staying on the potter's wheel, staying on that wheel, dying to self. He's the potter, we're the clay.

00:11:13.120 --> 00:11:19.033
We have this treasure in earthen vessels, that the excellency of the power will be known of him and not of us.

00:11:19.034 --> 00:11:35.686
I'm so desperate, and I thought, 'Why do I want so badly the anointing? Why do I want to see that? Is it for self-glory?'No.

00:11:35.687 --> 00:11:44.889
My heart, when I see children with special needs like my Megan, who is overcoming—she's getting better and better every day.

00:11:44.890 --> 00:11:59.064
When I see that, you feel helpless without it. There's nothing you can do in the natural to fix it other than the anointing and a prayer. So the more I see it, it comes out of my spirit.

00:11:59.065 --> 00:12:14.682
It comes out of my spirit to see children of Down's and to know that there's more, that God is a God that is able to heal, that he is a rewarder of those that diligently seek him.

00:12:14.683 --> 00:12:28.924
It's like when I, one person, sowed a seed, and I sowed it by faith, but it was a sacrificial seed for Diana and me. We did it recently.

00:12:28.925 --> 00:12:54.468
And they said, 'Well, we're believing for a hundredfold return.'And I said, 'But what I want is not monetary.'Truly, I try to stretch myself to believe for more because I know what it takes to have a staff, to hire somebody to help us.

00:12:54.469 --> 00:13:10.940
And that's going to take a lot of money to go and say, 'Well, I'm going to relieve Diana of all this pressure on Diana to answer all these emails and all this stuff all the time so she can focus on other things, to hire an employee.'Well, that's going to take money.

00:13:10.941 --> 00:13:19.043
Well, that stretches me. So I have to believe more, to believe God for somebody else's salary because they're dependent on you for their check.

00:13:19.044 --> 00:13:25.008
But the whole part of what I'm after is not money. I'm after God, and I want him.

00:13:25.009 --> 00:13:37.745
And in him, I want the anointing so bad, and I go, 'Lord, there's a balance of everything.'But I'm like, 'Man, don't you all understand what I'm saying?'I say, 'You just want to see the dead raised?

00:13:37.746 --> 00:13:43.287
You just want to see blinded eyes open. You want to see ears pop open.

00:13:43.288 --> 00:13:51.599
You want to see people get out of wheelchairs.'But you say, 'Well, Brandon, I've never seen that before.'But I know that it exists.

00:13:51.600 --> 00:13:59.194
There's a level of the anointing that I know exists. I've experienced it, but to maintain it and keep it and not get into the flesh...

00:13:59.195 --> 00:14:05.214
Like certain preachers that I've seen on platforms, they had a great anointing, but it seems like they've lost it now.

00:14:05.215 --> 00:14:17.275
It's not as strong, definitely. And I've seen a lot of them, and you go, 'Where's that fire? What happened? You had it in the '90s.

00:14:17.276 --> 00:14:33.563
You had it in the early 2000s, but then it just kind of died.'I don't want to be a flame that shrivels up, that goes away, that gets put out. I want to live long and finish strong.

00:14:33.564 --> 00:14:54.190
But I've told the Lord many times, if I'm not able to handle this, if I'm not able to preach the gospel to the nations and I'm going to stumble and fall like some of these people through trials—their moral failures or whatever.

00:14:54.191 --> 00:15:03.156
And you see what happened even in our old church. So many people were hurt. So many people turned away from the Lord.

00:15:03.157 --> 00:15:11.914
When you see a moral failure, when you see these things, if I'm not able to handle it, and I don't want to ever be arrogant and say that I am able to...

00:15:11.915 --> 00:15:16.590
'Oh, that would never happen to me,'because you see some of the greatest fall.

00:15:16.591 --> 00:15:31.517
I said, 'Lord, I'd rather not have it at all than cause a million people to fall.'That's what I'm trying to tell y'all, because of something that I don't see in myself.

00:15:31.518 --> 00:15:44.268
So I examine myself every day like that, because I see people on huge platforms that get really big, get a lot of money, and then they're ruined by it.

00:15:44.269 --> 00:15:55.420
I can name a bunch of them right now. But I don't judge them. I just don't want to be accountable for hurting people like that.

00:15:55.421 --> 00:16:04.238
Does that make sense? It's important to me to always be transparent, always be a person that...

00:16:04.239 --> 00:16:08.366
we all have stuff we're going through, folks. We're always...

00:16:08.367 --> 00:16:19.573
but I'm just me. I don't want to ever be exalted like you look at a celebrity. I'm just me.

00:16:19.574 --> 00:16:34.319
Now, I know there are certain lines when you show up at my PO box and you camp outside—like I'm mentioning somebody right now—and you demand to want to pray for my little girl and you say that God sent you to pray for her.

00:16:34.320 --> 00:16:43.674
And then you sit out there and you creep out the postal workers so much that they said if you show up again, they're calling the cops because you think that God's called you.

00:16:43.675 --> 00:16:47.672
Now, folks, I don't want to be... there's some weirdness out here in the body of Christ.

00:16:47.673 --> 00:16:52.810
There needs to be some stability. And I feel like it's not taught.

00:16:52.811 --> 00:17:01.304
You just don't go trying to lay hands on people's kids thinking because you feel like God's called you to. God didn't tell me that.

00:17:01.305 --> 00:17:17.051
And I don't know why I get off on that, but it is something that still bothers me, that there are people that are just consistently coming to my church trying to touch my kid because you feel you have an anointing on you to pray for my Megan.

00:17:17.052 --> 00:17:29.175
You'll never touch my child. Never. That's my child. And if God calls me to have somebody pray for my child, I'll take my child to that person.

00:17:29.176 --> 00:17:33.727
But you're not called to come laying hands on people unless God...

00:17:33.728 --> 00:17:39.225
unless I feel peace about it. And that's happened several times now.

00:17:39.226 --> 00:17:43.794
And it makes me, quite frankly, I get irate when I get in the car.

00:17:43.795 --> 00:17:52.344
I told... my son knows, everybody: do not touch my children. Do not touch me.

00:17:52.345 --> 00:17:58.090
That's why I said the Bible says do not lay hands on a man suddenly.

00:17:58.091 --> 00:18:09.607
And I do not, after encounters that I've had, I do not allow people to pray for me unless the Holy Spirit tells me to let them.

00:18:09.608 --> 00:18:16.861
I just don't. I would advise you to be wise about it too. You are not touching me.

00:18:16.862 --> 00:18:27.404
You're not touching my wife. You are not touching my children. So, it is what it is. But I felt like I need to say that.

00:18:27.405 --> 00:18:39.423
So, don't come to my PO box, try to knock on my house, find out where I live so you think you can lay hands on me and touch me or I'm going to touch you.

00:18:39.424 --> 00:18:47.714
Okay. God bless you. So, you know, I feel like it's important I say these things.

00:18:47.715 --> 00:18:55.162
There's an importance of the anointing and being hungry and impartation by the Spirit of God.

00:18:55.163 --> 00:19:02.978
But I don't need people laying hands on me for impartation. I need Jesus.

00:19:02.979 --> 00:19:12.493
I need Jesus in these last days, finding where it comes through prayer.

00:19:12.494 --> 00:19:16.617
Obviously, it comes through prayer, but it comes through sitting at his feet.

00:19:16.618 --> 00:19:25.481
Moses had an experience with a burning bush, and the Father was in the bush.

00:19:25.482 --> 00:19:30.399
I could go on. You can go on. David had this down, you know. Come on.

00:19:30.400 --> 00:19:37.201
There's so much impartation that didn't come from laying on hands, other than David had an impartation from the prophet.

00:19:37.202 --> 00:19:46.929
But I look and say, 'God, where are you? I just need you.'The Smith Wigglesworths, the John G.

00:19:46.930 --> 00:19:55.266
Lakes, the Kathryn Kuhlman's all had impartation from him sitting at his feet.

00:19:55.267 --> 00:20:06.365
I'm just desperate. I'm just desperate for an end-time move. I'm desperate for what we've not seen before.

00:20:06.366 --> 00:20:16.644
I know what's coming: the visions that I've had about the outpouring, the visions that I've had about the last outpouring of the healing revival and the demonstrations, the manifestations.

00:20:16.645 --> 00:20:28.617
And I thought, 'What is the domino to tip it?'Jesus did nothing without his Father. Nothing.

00:20:28.618 --> 00:20:36.112
Everything Jesus did was sitting at the Father's, going up in the mountains praying.

00:20:36.113 --> 00:20:46.558
Apart from him, he said, 'I do nothing.'So if Jesus did that, then what? That's what I'll do.

00:20:46.559 --> 00:20:57.953
Mary put—I've always said this—Mary put a demand on the anointing that was on Jesus's life at the marriage feast whenever he turned the water into wine.

00:20:57.954 --> 00:21:03.597
I know, putting a demand on it saying, 'Father, I thank you when you lay hands on someone that you're the healer.

00:21:03.598 --> 00:21:09.359
You're the deliverer.'I get that. But it's like the woman with the issue of blood.

00:21:09.360 --> 00:21:20.848
She reached out and touched the hem of the garment, and she put a demand on that anointing and she said, 'If I just touch the hem of his garment, I can be made whole.'Her faith made her whole.

00:21:20.849 --> 00:21:26.540
But she reached out in faith, and she grabbed onto something, and she pulled.

00:21:26.541 --> 00:21:34.277
She pulled. You pull in your spirit. You pull. It's like, 'I'm desperate.

00:21:34.278 --> 00:21:41.011
I'm desperate.'And in that desperation, he says, 'Those that seek me will find me.

00:21:41.012 --> 00:21:49.115
Those that knock, the door will be opened unto them.'So in desperation, I'm just seeking him.

00:21:49.116 --> 00:22:01.243
I'm pulling on that. 'Father, I need a touch. Father, I'm desperate. Father, I'm thirsty. Father, I need more of you.

00:22:01.244 --> 00:22:09.439
I need more revelation of you.'You say, 'I'm wall-to-wall Holy Ghost.'Then I need to give you more of me.

00:22:09.440 --> 00:22:15.486
Something's off because I want to be at the spout where the glory comes out. I want to be where he's at.

00:22:15.487 --> 00:22:22.680
I want that fire on me so strong that my shadow passes by and people are healed.

00:22:22.681 --> 00:22:28.130
Waking up every day with expectation for manifestation of the glory on your life.

00:22:28.131 --> 00:22:39.417
Not going and saying, 'Well, it's just another average day,'but when people see you, they see Jesus. Do you hear what I'm saying, folks?

00:22:39.418 --> 00:22:48.223
There is a point of that glory that I'm talking about where all this church politics—I'm so done with it.

00:22:48.224 --> 00:22:54.126
'Are you on my YouTube channel? Are you going to be on collabs?'All this stuff.

00:22:54.127 --> 00:23:07.377
I just want Jesus. 'Well, you didn't come to my conference and...'I just want Jesus.

00:23:07.378 --> 00:23:18.995
And who said we're going to feel a presence all the time? But that's what I'm after.

00:23:18.996 --> 00:23:29.220
I want him. I want him. I'm so desperate for him. I want a fresh drink every day.

00:23:29.221 --> 00:23:40.036
And I do these videos, and I try to be as vulnerable as I can to teach you all how I've done this through my life.

00:23:40.037 --> 00:23:48.013
It's very awkward. People have no idea—I mean, now it's grown to like 60,000 every day.

00:23:48.014 --> 00:24:02.874
Every time I do this, 60,000 people—it's a lot, and everybody has a critic about it, and it's just me being me.

00:24:02.875 --> 00:24:15.634
All I can do is just be me. I don't know how else to do it other than to try to teach you the intimacy of my relationship with him. And it's so intimate, and it's so personal to me.

00:24:15.635 --> 00:24:36.991
And it's like having so many people criticize it and you go, 'But it's pure to me.'All I know is that I love him and I seek him with all my heart because he's my friend, and in my desperation, he visits.

00:24:36.992 --> 00:24:45.351
All this other crap doesn't matter to me. It truly doesn't. Popularity, whether you show up or not, I just do it because he asked me to.

00:24:45.352 --> 00:24:51.821
If he tells me to stop tomorrow, I will. Trust me, it's more convenient for me to stop.

00:24:51.822 --> 00:25:00.248
But I do it. I do it because he said, 'I want you to do it for me.'And I said, 'I'll do it for you.

00:25:00.249 --> 00:25:06.102
Help me.'And it's not easy for my flesh because I'm a very reclusive person.

00:25:06.103 --> 00:25:11.410
I try to be real with people on social media, but I don't like them knowing my business.

00:25:11.411 --> 00:25:22.079
I don't like them in my circle, my space. In fact, I truly never even talked to my family. I've been that way my whole life.

00:25:22.080 --> 00:25:31.822
Really, a person who kind of goes in his room and just does his own thing, but I have intimacy with the Father and I just want to talk to him.

00:25:31.823 --> 00:25:43.752
Do you want a God that you can talk to? I'm not religious. It's a relationship with me.

00:25:43.753 --> 00:25:57.991
But I expect him to show up, just like I expect my wife to talk back to me if I'm talking to her in the car, and if she doesn't, I'll say, 'You're being rude,'or vice versa, right?

00:25:57.992 --> 00:26:08.131
Don't you in a relationship? Well, I expect him to talk. If you don't talk, you're being rude, right?

